GOI imposing export restrictions or require that export proceeds remain in the country to ensure domestic industries have access to scarce resources, to build up foreign exchange reserves, or to retain more value within the national economy falls under protectionist policy and strategy.

Author: nick3512
Content:
These are all great books, however, not sure to what extent it's applicable for Indonesian mkt. 

For example Warren Buffet, student of Ben Graham, he doesn't always visit a company before investing. Sometime, he was just relying on financial statement and non-official channel(?). In another words, he is relying on the integrity of the public accounting firm which, in the US, is not without scandal but still reliable enough due to regulation, code of ethics, standards of practice, etc. That said, not sure if we can totally relying on financial statement for Indonesian public companies? 

Note: I hv to admit, I am not following Indonesian companies and my view may not be based on the most updated information.

Author: murzzbow
Content:
> Upaya yang pertama, Pemerintah Indonesia akan memangkas beban 2 persen yang berasal dari reformasi administrasi perpajakan dan bea cukai. 
> 
> Kemudian langkah kedua adalah pemangkasan tarif Pajak Penghasilan (PPh) impor dari yang sebelumnya 2,5 persen menjadi hanya 0,5 persen. Hal ini diklaim dapat memangkas beban tarif tambahan sebesar 2 persen sehingga membuat total beban tarif turun menjadi sekitar 28 persen.
> 
> Langkah ketiga dilakukan melalui penyesuaian tarif bea masuk produk impor yang berasal dari AS dan masuk kategori most favored nation (MFN). Tarif yang semula dikenakan sebesar 5 persen hingga 10 persen, akan diturunkan menjadi 0 persen sampai 5 persen. 
> 
> Selanjutnya, Bendahara Negara itu juga menjanjikan penyesuaian terhadap tarif bea keluar untuk komoditas minyak sawit mentah atau crude palm oil (CPO), yang diklaim ekuivalen menurunkan beban pengusaha sebesar 5 persen. 
> 
> Selain itu, pemerintah juga tengah mempercepat proses trade remedies seperti bea masuk antidumping (BMAD), agar bisa diselesaikan hanya dalam 15 hari, dengan berkoordinasi bersama kementerian dan lembaga (K/L) terkait.

Author: unknownblue
Content:
*whether ideal or not, *both *have to be implemented*
the trick is who you are acting as, time, and scale.
while the key is prioritiziation.
in simple math: 50 kuadrat + 50 kuadrat is less than 60 kuadrat + 40 Kuadrat

Which to be fair, you wouldnt know unless u studied it religiously, or has practiced irl.

Local economy has to be developed, but it wouldnt develop fast enough without a port

whats needed on the government side is to focus on infrastructure: Port, cold storage, financing, incentives etc.

Whats needed on the private sector: is to take full advantage of the incentives, or even be the missing gap govt didnt fulfill. 

but rural areas doesnt always have those conglomerates with huge money to blow and make a port.

*here we enter LGFV*
Making a port has to begin from central government assistance *initially*. not fully
governments are allowed to open tender, or invite cooperation to build those port and take cuts as its finished or be paid back in loans.

i.e biaya individu/tiket jalan toll dan MRT itu dibayar ke indonesia, dan ke negara partner yag bantu buat, such as "JICA, AFD, UAE, Saudi, etc"

while government would then use other marketting scheme such as ads untuk bayar loan itu.


The big question. "Masyarakat lokal gimana???"
honestly... Bodo amat.

job absorbtion, local livelihood etc
kan bakal dapet dari CSR dan datengnya perusahan dari luar yg bakal kerja bareng?

atau ga perusahaan lokal kita dorong masuk ke international deals, disini fungsi investment board pada kabupaten yang menjadi collateral for int. or cross border/island/province deals

that way local companies can elevate themselves

tapi kalau lokal ga bisa compete gmna?
well goodluck... ur region is fucked over because ur leaders are too corrupt, lazy, or stupid

mostly lazy

Content:
Itâ€™s as growing as china. The reason why Indian tech tends to migrate to the US is because the pay is better and there is less competition for them (compared to India). First preference for Indian tech is US because of that. Plus, you canâ€™t beat an offer by MAANG (Meta Amazon Apple Netflix Google). 

Indian tech choose Aus because of work-life balance, and the possibility of getting permanent residency is easier than US.

Those with finance expertise will choose either Singapore or Dubai because these are financial hubs and career progression is quite fast. Plus, tax is lower and package is better than India.

To give some perspective, my role is worth 2x more salary in the US, and the exposure Iâ€™d get would be way more diverse than Aus.

In India, itâ€™s so hard to find that on sosmed these days without being attacked by crazy Hindutvas. Theyâ€™re too nationalistic and a nuisance tbh. Most progressives treat them like cockroaches - ignore them or tell them to f* off.

Migration of skilled workers to other countries usually is because of itâ€™s an easier option for Indians rather than being stuck in a pressure cooker situation in India.

[BREAKING NEWS] Summary Hasil Meeting BEI-MSCI

ðŸ‘‡ðŸ‘‡ðŸ‘‡ðŸ‘‡

- Meeting OJK, BEI, KSEI, Danantara dengan MSCI berjalan positif & konstruktif.
- MSCI fokus ke 2 isu utama: transparansi kepemilikan saham & likuiditas pasar.

Transparansi:
- Data pemegang saham bakal dibuka lebih detail, bukan cuma di atas 5%, tapi hingga 1%.
- Klasifikasi investor di KSEI diperinci dari 9 tipe jadi 27 sub-tipe, biar beneficial ownership lebih jelas.

Likuiditas:
- Indonesia ajukan proposal kenaikan free float minimum dari 7,5% ke 15%.
- Penerapan dilakukan bertahap, nggak langsung dipukul rata.

- MSCI terbuka dan kooperatif, bahkan siap kasih guidance teknis soal metodologi penilaian.
- Akan ada pembahasan lanjutan di level teknis.
- OJK berkomitmen update progres ke publik secara rutin.

Author: sukadeltoro
Content:
Q2-Q3 tetep fokus Danantara yang jadi risk taker + market maker yang paling gede, BI (sesuai dengan MoU tahun lalu, jadi last resort buyer buat bonds pemerintah) mungkin bakal beli bonds pemerintah in these Q2-Q3 untuk ngasih sinyal stabilitas/bemper buat APBN 2027

Considering global uncertainty, APBN 2027 bakal: Defence, MBG, PSN, and pendidikan (Sekolah rakyat and Garuda) + fiscal space buat implementasi CEPA Indonesia-EU and CEPA Indonesia-Canada

Expect more swasembada + substitusi energi karena indo more likely derisking dari semua global uncertainties, due to limited policy room to wiggle

Expect conditional/tactical energy deal in trade negotiations, as leverage to hedge and to balance

CEPA Indo-GCC/GCC members? Probably, liat UAE and KSA as benchmarks gimana (risk profile KSA lumayan tinggi) 

CEPA Indonesia-Mexico? Jadi alt route ke US selain Canada, masih lama sih

Africa and Latam? Tergantung Mercosur and AU, liat behaviour China and US gimana di Latam + Chinese infra di East and Central Africa

@ : "Kamu dari jurusan?"

@ : "Skripsi dan penelitian kamu tentang apa?"
& : "Eh... Manfaat memelihara ikan cupang terhadap kesehatan mental masyarakat"

Dan dia tinggal SEMHAS, gimana ceritanya judul begitu bisa lewat sampai SEMHAS? Jangankan berkaitan dengan jurusan, sikit pun ga nyangkut dengan mata kuliah mereka selama 4 tahun. 

Ditanya bisa ngoding? Kagak... Ditanya tentang networking dan security, gapaham... 

Kalau buah busuk 1, oke masih normal... Ini ditanya ke yang lain malah jawabannya pada sama... 

Kadang ada yang judulnya kelihatan _Wah_ tapi agak aneh... Kayak 'Analisa Potensi Penerapan AI untuk menggantikan tenaga kerja petani di Bireuen'... Apalah, coba?

Author: buzzer9229
Content:
Current dating market is fucked:
-Standards are affected by social media content
-Capitalism is affecting how we view relations: materialistic and readiness dependent
-Market logic seeps into dating, suddenly people are treated as "options"
-Too much avoidants leaving little room for growth and too much anxious people setting too high expectations
-Sex is commodified, and people tend to project fantasies instead of building relationships

Author: buzzer9229
Content: The boring "if they leave you, grind and focus on yourself and make sure you're irresistable and unable to ignore" bs is oversaturing dating logic

Author: buzzer9229
Content: People forget that the most important thing to have before you enter the chase is to make sure you're content and happy with yourself first, so that if things fall apart, you don't really lose anything

Author: buzzer9229
Content: But these days most people think that happiness comes from being with someone else or having someone else

Author: plem1nika
Content:
Agreed, also my take on this is that our generation is so well-versed in emotional fluency but without emotional accountability and we are conditioned to get used to it. I personally was introduced to so many psychological frameworks through social media, (be it attachment styles, love languages, trauma responses, self-awareness) I didn't know there was a name for it, and I thought naming the dysfunction would lead to an easy fix (we can just google it, or ask people online) obvi not ðŸ™„. Previous generations tend to be ignorant when faced with relationship problems but our generation hides behind reasoning to *pre-justify* harm like "told ya I'm emotionally unavailable", "it's just my trauma, thought you'd understand", "I warned you that I'm avoidant, so it's not you"
Likeee why do we keep on explaining it better instead of stopping ourselves from causing pain to others?

So many demands and nuances for love, abdi oge hoyong dikanyaah

Author: petrachristalbert
Content:
Parah banget wkkwkwkw... Ada rapat tertutup yang diadakan para pemimpin kelompokÂ² GAM di Aceh Besar. NamaÂ² orang yang mengaku pemimpin disana itu cukup asing. 

Mereka duduk, membahas sampai saling memprovokasi satu sama lain, membahas terkait 'Penghinaan kepada korban banjir yang dianggap seperti ternak mati' serta 'Penghinaan terhadap adat Meugang Aceh oleh Presiden ditengah - tengah kondisi Aceh yang masih terpuruk'. 

Pembahasannya cukup mencekam, semua marahÂ². Tapi uniknya gaada yang beradu pas pemilihan ketua sementara dalam mengorganisir rencana mereka. Hmmmmm... 

Tapi disela sela pembahasan, mereka mention tentang 'Buzzer' serta 'antekÂ² pemerintah'. Mereka pada adu pengalaman terhadap pemerintah, dan sampai ada 1 orang dengan gelar Tengku angkat bicara, "Saya pernah, dipaksa buat dukung si Prabowo itu. Mau jadi pendukung si Prabowo itu." Disini masih logis lah... Sampai keluar kalimat selanjutnya, "Saya ditelepon langsung sama si Prabowo! 'Kamu dukung saya, bakal saya beri Aceh ini sama mu'. Saya jawab, 'Saya tidak mau! Allahuakbar!'." 

Dan yap, saya ga tau apa ini udah disusupi provokator, apakah cuman informan saya yang masuk ke rapat ini atau... 

Yang penting, mereka berencana untuk membuat masalah, dan perkumpulan kali ini skalanya juga bukan hanya tingkah kumpulan 1 kecamatan...
